section.section:
The only issues that may be contested are:
the identity of the employee;
whether there is an underlying court order requiring the employee to provide health insurance coverage for the employee's child;
that the amount of the withholding exceeds the limits of the federal Consumer Credit Protection Act; and
that the child for whom health insurance coverage is sought is emancipated.

The only issues that may be contested in an administrative hearing are:
the identity of the employee;
whether there is an underlying court order requiring the employee to provide health insurance coverage for the employee's child;
that the amount of the withholding exceeds the limits of the federal Consumer Credit Protection Act; and
that the child for whom health insurance coverage is sought is emancipated.
